我先自引一段话："民主党一班人水平太低，他们总是发力过猛，结果总是砸到自己头上" 现实总会惊人相似地重演某些历史剧情。而民主党人将再一次进入“死亡螺旋”之路。当川普周六推特炸弹出来后，MSM说了什么？"No evidence", "baseless accusation"，right？但哪一家媒体在攻击川普及其团队与邪恶俄国人勾结时摆出过任何直接证据？当民主党全党上下一心按着希拉里的剧本演出时，用“17个情报部门证实”川普及其团队与邪恶俄国人勾结的说法时，谁提供过任何任何直接证据？现在民主党议员们纷纷跳出来说川普的指责"No fact back up“。这几天包括直到今天的白宫新闻会上，几个MSM记者仍在追问Sean Spicer是否川普有证据。最有份量的攻击是以参院大老Chuck Schumer和众院情报委员会的康州议员Jim Hines为代表的精心构陷。他们这么说：川普总统要么错在用没有事实根据来指责前总统，这是非常严重的政治错误。要么如果川普总统真地有证据，哪错误就更严重，因为他是将FISA批准的合法收集的高度绝密信息违法地泄露出来了，这就远非一般的错误了。无论如何，总之他错了。这个构陷的含义是：谅你拿不出“证据”（因为能成为证据的东西是绝密的，所以是不能拿出来的），但你要敢拿出来就是犯法因而是犯罪。这里“证据”指的是：到底所谓俄国人hack的证据是怎么回事，到底有关与俄国人的通话/勾结的机密/绝密情报来源是怎么回事，以及有没有对川普及其团队进行了非法截听。这个Vault 7提供了与有关上述“证据”的信息：CIA伪造了俄国人的hack的fake news（而参众两院的情报委员会竟然都信以为真，炒作了大半年），CIA曾大规模地侵入了各种手机，电脑以及smart TV，随时随地监控和截听任意想获取的“情报”。于是，对Flynn, Sessions以及川普团队包括川普本人的监听仅由Vault 7文件就可以间接证实了，然而真相是：美国情报部门的绝大多数行动根本不需要什么FISA批准。民主党人自以为聪明的FISA批准说顿时土崩瓦解，一地鸡毛。最愚蠢不可救的就是民主党人可了劲地天天打俄国牌，用力过猛，却忘了即使没有维基解密，总统也是可以看所有绝密文件这个事实（拿某情报官员的话说：总统是所有情报部门的客户），也忘了现在司法部，CIA和国土安全部都是川普的内阁，他们都有权查看这些部门的所有文件这个事实。难道民主党人居然以为奥巴马政府先前搞的那些事，尤其是对搞政敌的那些事所涉及的资料这些部门能全部毁掉吗？请注意昨天国土安全部长John Kelly在CNN采访上被问到“证据”时这么说：”总统之所以那么说自有他的道理，因为他确信有的事情的确发生过“（If the President of State said that， he's got his reasons to say that, he's got some convincing evidence that took place）。还值得注意的是川普的前竞选班子经理Lewandowski在接受Fox采访时说的话：所谓Sessions两次与俄国大使谈话，一次在共和党大会上，另一次在参议员办公室，实际上都被监听了。当时采访他的Fox主持人Judge Jeanine吓了一跳追问道：“你是在说Flynn还是Sessions？你是说在Sessions参议员的办公室里也被监听了？” Lewandowski回答说：“是的。”姑且理论上假定有这么回事，那么在共和党大会那种场合，在参议员办公室那种场合怎么监听Sessions？难道民主党人还能说FISA批准对一个参议员进行监听？可以说Vault 7非常完美地回答了这个问题。最后不得不提一提一位著名的猪队友，就是那位曾在在2013年国会听证会上作伪证的NSA的头目James Clapper，在川普周六推特炸弹出来后他立即到电视上否认对川普进行过监听。他的理论是：如果有的话，那么就会有FISA批件，而如果有FISA批件，那他就会知道。他打包票说，因为他不知道有过那样的FISA批件，所以没有监听那回事情。一个敢在国会under oath的情况下公然撒谎作伪证的人，在没有under oath时说没有就没有？James Clapper那次作伪证就是否认NSA有过对所有美国公民大规模的非法收集电话电邮的行动。但之后不久”棱镜门“便爆发了，James Clapper作伪证罪坐实。然而奇怪地是他没有被追究。结论：即使没有“Vault 7门”，奥巴马政府所干过的各种劣政也难逃被追究的命运。“Vault 7门”可不是“棱镜门”的简单重演，而是奥巴马为民主党人留下的凄美的“死亡螺旋”。

follow.user_name: 抢到了一个经典的名字

Senior Doctor Admiral General Profesor Master Dicklord Baron Archduke Marmaduke Viceroy Admiral Wing Command (Did I Mention Admiral?) Ali Ackbar Dickwad (US Listeni/bəˈrɑːk huːˈseɪn oʊˈbɑːmə/;[1][2] born August 4, 1961) is the 44th and current President of the United States. He is the first African American to hold the office and the first president born outside the continental United States. Born in Honolulu, Hawaii, Obama is a graduate of Columbia University and Harvard Law School, where he was president of the Harvard Law Review. He was a community organizer in Chicago before earning his law degree. He worked as a civil rights attorney and taught constitutional law at the University of Chicago Law School between 1992 and 2004. While serving three terms representing the 13th District in the Illinois Senate from 1997 to 2004, he ran unsuccessfully in the Democratic primary for the United States House of Representatives in 2000 against incumbent Bobby Rush.

In 2004, Obama received national attention during his campaign to represent Illinois in the United States Senate with his victory in the March Democratic Party primary, his keynote address at the Democratic National Convention in July, and his election to the Senate in November. He began his presidential campaign in 2007 and, after a close primary campaign against Hillary Clinton in 2008, he won sufficient delegates in the Democratic Party primaries to receive the presidential nomination. He then defeated Republican nominee John McCain in the general election, and was inaugurated as president on January 20, 2009. Nine months after his inauguration, Obama was named the 2009 Nobel Peace Prize laureate.

During his first two years in office, Obama signed into law economic stimulus legislation in response to the Great Recession in the form of the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009 and the Tax Relief, Unemployment Insurance Reauthorization, and Job Creation Act of 2010. Other major domestic initiatives in his first term included the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act, often referred to as "Obamacare"; the Dodd–Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act; and the Don't Ask, Don't Tell Repeal Act of 2010. In foreign policy, Obama ended U.S. military involvement in the Iraq War, increased U.S. troop levels in Afghanistan, signed the New START arms control treaty with Russia, ordered U.S. military involvement in Libya in opposition to Muammar Gaddafi, and ordered the military operation that resulted in the death of Osama bin Laden. In January 2011, the Republicans regained control of the House of Representatives as the Democratic Party lost a total of 63 seats; and, after a lengthy debate over federal spending and whether or not to raise the nation's debt limit, Obama signed the Budget Control Act of 2011 and the American Taxpayer Relief Act of 2012.

Obama was reelected president in November 2012, defeating Republican nominee Mitt Romney, and was sworn in for a second term on January 20, 2013. During his second term, Obama has promoted domestic policies related to gun control in response to the Sandy Hook Elementary School shooting, and has called for greater inclusiveness for LGBT Americans, while his administration has filed briefs which urged the Supreme Court to strike down part of the federal Defense of Marriage Act and state level same-sex marriage bans as unconstitutional. In foreign policy, Obama ordered U.S. military intervention in Iraq in response to gains made by ISIL after the 2011 withdrawal from Iraq, continued the process of ending U.S. combat operations in Afghanistan, promoted discussions that led to the 2015 Paris Agreement on global climate change, brokered a nuclear deal with Iran, and normalized U.S. relations with Cuba.
